444 based on the report.'
5 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
6 number to read consecutively.
7 SUMMARY
88 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. It directs the Governor's Energy
99 Office to coordinate with state agencies that permit, regulate or provide state assistance to
1100 renewable energy construction projects, including, but not limited to, the Department of
1111 Environmental Protection, the Department of Labor, the Department of Agriculture,
1122 Conservation and Forestry and the Public Utilities Commission, to evaluate how to display
1133 and maintain data regarding renewable energy construction projects in an efficient,
1144 meaningful and publicly accessible manner for the purposes of identifying renewable
1155 energy trends in Maine, including through the development of a database. The evaluation
1166 must provide a method to make the data publicly available and, to the extent practicable, a
1177 method for obtaining information from renewable energy construction developers. The
1188 amendment establishes evaluation criteria that the office must use in conducting the
1199 evaluation. The office must submit a report on the evaluation to the Joint Standing
2200 Committee on Energy, Utilities and Technology by February 1, 2026, and the committee
2211 may report out a bill based on the office's report.
